This is a Windows Add-on available in Windows XP Pro or Windows XP Media Center editions of Windows XP. Open Control Panel from the Start Menu. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on Add or Remove Programs{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4d/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4d/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click on Add/Remove Windows Components{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8e/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select Internet Information Services from the Windows Component Wizard{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cb/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select Next. The Wizard may prompt you for your XP Installation Disc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

IIS 5.1 will now be installed{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f3/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f3/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

First go to the Control Panel again and click "Performance and Maintenance" and then navigate to "Administrative Tools". (For Service Pack 3, click directly on "Administrative Tools"){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/74/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now you should see "Internet Information Services"; open the program up (You may create a shortcut on the desktop so it is easier to find). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click next. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select "Select new security settings from template". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Click next. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select "Public Site". Now just keep clicking next until it is finished. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Configure-IIS-for-Windows-XP-Pro-Step-13Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
